sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>(Browser)
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NotebookCtrl as odh-notebook-controller
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KubeRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    participant IDE as JupyterLab/code-server/RStudio<br/>8888 or 8787/TCP HTTP
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
    Note over User,IDE: Flow 1: User Launches Workbench
    User->>Dashboard: Select workbench image<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth (OpenShift)
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>NotebookCtrl: Notify (watch event)
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>+ inject kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull workbench image<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull Secret
    Registry-->>K8sAPI: Container image layers
    Note over K8sAPI: Pod starts:<br/>IDE + kube-rbac-proxy<br/>+ NGINX (if code-server/RStudio)
    User->>KubeRBAC: Access workbench<br/>HTTPS/8443, OAuth Token
    KubeRBAC->>K8sAPI: Validate token (SubjectAccessReview)<br/>HTTPS/6443
    K8sAPI-->>KubeRBAC: Auth OK
    KubeRBAC->>IDE: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8888 (localhost, plaintext)
    IDE-->>KubeRBAC: Notebook UI response
    KubeRBAC-->>User: HTTPS response (TLS 1.3)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Elyra Pipeline Execution
    User->>IDE: Define pipeline in Elyra UI
    IDE->>KFP: Submit pipeline<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    KFP->>K8sAPI: Create pipeline pod<br/>(uses runtime image)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull runtime image<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull Secret
    Registry-->>K8sAPI: Runtime container image
    Note over K8sAPI: Pipeline pod starts<br/>(runtime-minimal/datascience/pytorch/etc.)
    K8sAPI->>S3: Fetch notebook inputs<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS credentials
    S3-->>K8sAPI: Notebook + data artifacts
    Note over K8sAPI: Execute notebook<br/>(headless Python)
    K8sAPI->>S3: Store outputs<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS credentials
    S3-->>K8sAPI: Upload confirmation
    end
